  "news": [
    {
      "title": "Credits & Multiplayer now live in the real menu scene, camera craning to the castle",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Dropped the separate campfire scene. Both pages stay on the live key-art (clouds/fog still moving) while a new push param on MenuBackground.render slowly cranes the framing toward the distant castle. Shared cinematic title-card: letterbox bars ease in, a soft scrim darkens only the left edge, and the names fade in as a left-aligned column with a big ember-gold hero. Minimal Return hint, no box. UI stays under 20% of the screen."
    },
    {
      "title": "Credits are a campfire now — found a fire still burning in the woods at dusk",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Replaced the credits panel with a full in-world scene drawn from the 2D primitives: evening sky gradient + stars + drifting cloud, two parallax pine-silhouette rows with fog, a flickering layered campfire with rising embers, fireflies, and a slow handheld camera sway. The names fade in over the fire (no panel) on a timeline, hero name pulsing in ember-gold. Only control is a carved Return plank that warms and bobs on hover. Ambience: wind, distant birds, faint fire crackle. Respects Reduce Motion."
    },
    {
      "title": "Fix cramped Credits/Multiplayer pages — text no longer runs under the button",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "The panels were too short for the copy, so body text overlapped the Back button. Rebuilt both pages: vertically-centred panel, a fenced footer (divider + bottom-anchored button) the text can't collide with, tighter wording, and a hero wordmark with room to breathe. Panel heights are derived from content now."
    },
    {
      "title": "Gave the menus a proper pass — one consistent look across every screen",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Every menu page now shares one design language: same panels, same buttons, and a gold stamp-and-rule header (drawPanelHeader). Added a danger button style that tints red on focus for Quit / Save & Leave / Delete."
    },
    {
      "title": "Fix: die in the void instead of falling forever out of the world",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Falling past the world floor (y < -16) now applies heavy continuous damage (14 hp/s) with a heart flash, ending at the death screen with 'You fell out of the world.' ~1.5s from full health, so it reads as suffocating in the void rather than an endless fall."
    },
    {
      "title": "Fix: register furnace crafting recipe (8 cobblestone ring)",
      "date": "2026-06-19",
      "body": "The furnace system shipped in 0.4.0 but the crafting recipe itself was never registered, so a correct 8-cobble ring produced no output. Added a ring() shape check (cobblestone -> furnace) plus a progtest case. 30/30 checks pass."
    },
    {
      "title": "Furnaces, smelting, tool progression: iron/diamond tools, durability, mining tiers",
      "date": "2026-06-19",
      "body": "Smelting: added Sand->Glass alongside iron/gold ore; data-driven smelt map. Fuel system generalised off coal-only - Coal=8 smelts, Logs/Planks=1.5, Wooden tools=1; burn + cook progress persist."
    },
    {
      "title": "Underground generation fix: claustrophobic 2011-style caves + scarce uniform ores",
      "date": "2026-06-19",
      "body": "Caves: removed open caverns, tightened tunnel radius, added a second crossing tunnel system for dense maze-like networks. Ravines rarer/narrower/deeper, exposing tunnels. Mineshafts descend deeper with plank walkways and log supports."
    }
  ],
